Description:
Superb warehouse conversion, iconic city-fringe setting
Once a hive of activity in Foy & Gibson's illustrious retail heyday, now a spacious oasis of modern living; this superb apartment is a model of Melbourne's post-industrial evolution made for an exciting city-fringe lifestyle. Whitewashed extra-thick brickwork, polished hardwood floorboards, a broad bank of windows to Little Oxford Street and an historic barn door all add iconic character to the brilliant design of this impressively-proportioned warehouse conversion. Set quietly to the rear on the second floor, this light-filled apartment extends over 140 sqms (approx.) and also includes a secure car space on title. Located at Collingwood's vibrant heart, the secluded space is both an outstanding single-level sanctuary and a handy springboard to nearby Smith/Brunswick/Gertrude Streets, trams, East Melbourne hospitals, the city and elegant local parks and gardens. Have a poke around the area and get hooked on a daily discovery of fabulous cafes, restaurants, specialty shops and galleries. Immaculately presented with Nobo heating, LED lighting and new carpets, this striking home features wide entrance hallway with in-built storage cupboards, 2 huge bedrooms with mirror BIRs, central bathroom, laundry, large kitchen with brand new stainless-steel appliances and a substantial open-plan living and dining room. Be a part of history in an exceptional contemporary context and make this sensational warehouse conversion an essential part of your new life.
Insights: 18/93 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2020 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Spacious Queens Parade Shopfront & Dwelling
Expressions of Interest Closing Friday 5th June 2020 at 1:00pm
This outstanding double-storey shop and residence represents a prime landholding with an attractive presence amidst the retail hustle and bustle of the Queens Parade Village. One of a select cluster of extra-deep properties with a north-facing rear courtyard and direct laneway access for off-street parking, this Victorian shopfront building on a 240 sqm allotment (approx.) is Commercial 1 zoned adjoining popular retailers all benefitting from the wide footpath space, village atmosphere and proximity to public transport. Situated in the busy Neighbourhood Activity Centre Precinct on 'Melbourne's first major road', the landmark Queens Parade location with its cafes, restaurants and specialty shops is an enduring, exciting and rewarding retail hub where this unique 8-room opportunity offers a spacious, well-exposed shopfront, functional dwelling and exceptional potential. Offered with vacant possession and a range of commercial and residential options (STCA), the building includes open-plan retail POS area/showroom, kitchen, bathroom, living rooms, bedrooms, storerooms, large rear courtyard and secure on-site parking.
In conjunction with Kelly & Shiel | Damien Shiel 0419 394 999
** Inspections strictly by registration - Please contact the listing agent to arrange. Our inspection guidelines and policies for attendance can be viewed by visiting: https://bit.ly/CollinsSimmsCOVID-19 **

Description:
CHIC STYLE WITH THE CITY AT YOUR DOORSTEP
Currently leased until October 2020
Ideally situated between the banks of the iconic Yarra River and the convenience of Victoria Street in Abbotsford, this thoughtfully designed apartment is the perfect amalgamation of urban green oasis and city-edge living. Commute to work via bike on the Capital City Trail, or jump on a tram practically on your doorstep.
As you step inside, you're welcomed by the open plan living and dining area. A designer kitchen features quality Miele appliances, fittings, and smart storage. Offering a spacious two bedroom design with a shared bathroom and private balcony. Bonus features include heating/cooling, European-style laundry, video intercom, and a secure car space.
The position offers the best of both worlds: nature and convenience. Moments from Victoria Gardens Shopping Centre, Yarra Bend hiking and bike trails, famed restaurants & shops of Victoria Street, Richmond and Collingwood whilst trams, grocery, child care and cafe are ideally located at your door. "Precinct" features everything you'd expect from luxury city-edge living: an indoor 20 metre swimming pool, landscaped gardens, fully equipped gymnasium, on-site café, on-site child care centre, and manicured gardens.
Conditions of entry - IDENTIFICATION and contact number required, otherwise entry may be refused.
The information about this property has been supplied to us by the property owner, while we have no cause to doubt its accuracy, we provide no guarantee. We cannot attest to the functionality of any fixtures, fittings or inclusions to the property. Land and apartment dimensions and floor/site plans are supplied by third parties. Typing mistakes, omissions, transposing can occur, we provide to assist but make no representation. Buyers must carry out their own due diligence.

Description:
From shoe factory to luxurious residence: the ultimate conversion
***Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.***
Constructed within the shell of the former Cadet Shoe Factory, this ultra-spacious 4BR /3 BATH residence has all the ingredients for superbly-zoned family and work-from-home living. In a prime position, strolling distance to 2 tram routes, North Fitzroy and Nicholson Villages, schools and the Edinburgh Gardens, this light-filled north facing home, fringed by 4 outdoor living areas, with spectacular CBD and northern views, offers 4 double bedrooms (one with striking semi-ensuite bathroom and private deck); an expansive living/dining area open to a stunning kitchen (Siemens dual ovens and induction cooktop) and wide al fresco entertaining terrace; impressive family bathroom and 3rd bathroom/laundry, plus internal-entry double garage. Combining heritage appeal with low-maintenance contemporary design, this outstanding home features split-system air conditioning and custom storage throughout, polished hardwood floors, superior inclusions, video intercom, security alarm and a rain water recycle tank.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

What an address -- in the heart of North Fitzroy Village, minutes from leading cafes, two tram routes, the Circle bike path, schools and the Edinburgh Gardens! PLEASE REGISTER YOUR INTEREST IN ATTENDING THE OPEN FOR INSPECTION SO THAT WE CAN ENSURE COMPLIANCE WITH THE LATEST REGULATIONS
Please also register your interest to attend the auction so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations and be contacted in the event the property is going to be sold prior.
With its impeccable presentation, quality enhancements and abundance of natural light throughout, this semi-detached Victorian terrace presents an outstanding inner-urban lifestyle opportunity with enviably easy access to the best of Northcote. Beyond the allure of its eternally-attractive facade, discover a previously extended interior showcasing three bedrooms, all with built-in robes complemented by a period-style central bathroom complete with clawfoot tub. The light-filled lounge is both wide and versatile and leads through to the updated kitchen/meals area with breakfast bar, tiled splashbacks, stainless steel cooking appliances and dishwasher. Other features of this captivating home include gas heater (lounge), high ceilings and solid timber floors, plus double doors to a sizeable entertaining deck with elevated outlook and private rear courtyard garden. Move in, relax, and take full advantage of the home's premier location walking distance to High Street trams, cafes and shops, close to popular schools (zoned to Northcote HS), Northcote Station, Merri Creek trails and All Nations Park.

If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. Description:
Seamless style on the city's fringe
Seize this opportunity to live on the edge of the city with impressive skyline views and lifestyle benefits to match this stylish 2-bedroom apartment. Designed to impress with light saturated open plan living and entertaining serviced by a fabulous island stone kitchen, s/s appliances encompassing gas cooktop, integrated dishwasher and sleek grey toned splashback. Enjoy a sunset drink on an adjoining undercover balcony overlooking this vibrant locale.
The bedrooms are smartly appointed with BIRs serviced by a quality fully tiled bathroom with in-wall cistern WC. Relish the close proximity to Victoria Street and its bustling eateries along with Yarra Bend Park and a myriad of cycling/foot trails, trams, trains and buses to get you anywhere you need to go. Moments to Victoria Gardens, cinemas and IKEA for all your apartment's decor needs. Close to the city for bars, theatre shows, premium shopping and dining, boasting the life you have always dreamed of!
Couples, professionals, downsizers and investors will be equally impressed by this eye-catching apartment. Offering secure keypad entry, lift access, intercom and shared residential swimming pool and gymnasium. Additionally, providing split system heating/cooling, Euro laundry and modern flooring/blinds.

Positioned for absolute convenience, this Victorian-inspired home provides an exceptional city-edge lifestyle opportunity with its open design, quality inclusions and immediate access to some of Northcote's key attractions and amenities. Beyond the captivating facade, discover a warm and inviting interior comprising two large bedrooms (both with built-in robes) along with a uniquely stylish central bathroom with stone-top vanity and floor-to-ceiling marble tiling. Add to this a light-filled open lounge/dining area accompanied by a well-appointed kitchen complete with stainless steel cooking appliances, granite benchtops and splashbacks. Other stand-out features include high ornate ceilings and solid hardwood floors, reverse-cycle split-system air conditioning and additional Nobo panel heaters, solar power and heat pump hot water service, plus a private paved courtyard with secure off-street parking via the rear ROW. City-bound trams virtually at your doorstep, it's also walking distance to Merri Station, High Street's endless array of cafes and restaurants, Northcote High School, as well as Merri Creek Trails and acres of parkland.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you

A contemporary town residence of the highest calibre, sophisticated streamlined design and sun drenched interiors combine to create a home with wide ranging appeal. Description:
City-edge convenience
Please register your interest in attending the open for inspection so that we can ensure compliance with the latest regulations.
This modern light-filled apartment, superbly positioned adjacent to Yarra parkland and the Boathouse, close to Fairfield and Queens Parade shops and transport, offers a perfect design for low-maintenance living. A perfect property from the first home buyer, investor and downsizer it comprises an open plan kitchen/living area flowing to a private balcony, modern kitchen and stylish amenities are included in this property with two bedrooms, sleek bathroom/laundry. Including lift entry and secure parking, this immaculate residence features japanned oak floors, extensive storage, video intercom, and all the bells and whistles.
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
If you're attending an open for inspection, we request that you only attend if you are fit and healthy to do so and not under any self-isolation conditions. We request that you maintain a healthy distance from anyone attending the open for inspection, including other prospective buyers and our team members, and if requested wait outside so as to reduce the number of people in the property at any one time. Lastly, please refrain from touching items/fixtures and doors within the properties. If you would like to view something in particular, please request the agent's assistance. Thank you.

Description:
Above and beyond...
***This property is available for inspection by appointment - Please contact us to arrange a suitable time***
Breathtaking views of the city skyline from the huge private terrace of this boutique podium level townhouse. Enter through the security foyer and up to the second floor to where you find a spacious 2 level residence with a huge kitchen open plan living and
entertaining area leading onto the spacious terrace. Upstairs are three generous bedrooms, master with ensuite and balcony with more stunning views, a central bathroom and study nook. There is side by side secure parking for 2 cars, timber floors, quality finishes and a location central and convenient to public transport, shops restaurants, and the MCG. You're so close to the city you feel like you can reach out and touch it.

Description:
The rarest of opportunities, a blank canvas with so many possibilities
This corner allotment offers three street frontages with a North facing orientation and the perfect setting to build your own residence (STCA) in the heart of Fitzroy. Available at last, this rare vacant allotment of 130sqm (approx) is zoned Neighbourhood Residential 1 and is primed for you to create a brand new residence tailored to suit you. The options are endless with this fantastic opportunity and set within minutes from Brunswick Street's shops, cafes , parks and public transport. Be sure not to miss out on what is one of the very few vacant blocks in Fitzroy.

Description:
Delightful Living, Superb Locale
Beyond the charming white picket fence, this well presented three bedroom home offers sanctuary to anyone wanting a Northcote postcode. High ceilings balance a spacious living area opening to a feature wall and meals/study nook and fully equipped kitchen with ample cabinetry. The decked alfresco is perfect for entertaining, while the backyard has laneway access for car entry. Bright double sized bedrooms contain BIRs and the central bathroom features a floating basin, open shower and toilet. Including floorboards throughout, heating/cooling, Euro laundry, alarm system, garden shed and loft storage. Located between vibrant High Street and St. Georges Road, it's a brisk stroll to Northcote Plaza and public transport. Zoned to Northcote High with easy access to Brunswick Street and CBD.

Description:
PERFECTLY LOCATED INNER-NORTH LIVING
A terrific opportunity to secure this conveniently located apartment in sought-after Northcote. Comprising 1 bedroom with BIR, ensuite, open plan living/dining area, galley-style kitchen plus off-street car space. A smart investment for a first-time buyer or astute investor looking to add to their portfolio.
Take a short stroll to popular Westgarth and enjoy an array of cafes & eateries, Fairfield Boathouse, Northcote Park and T.H. Westfield Reserve. Direct access to Melbourne CBD by bus or train via Dennis Station.
Inspection by appointment only
CORONAVIRUS: Prevention Protection
As news of Coronavirus COVID -19 continues to make headlines Moss Estate Agents are following best practice precautionary measures to minimize risk to staff and clients. Together we can support one another to minimize the risk by taking reasonable safety measures. We will continue to provide a service to clients wishing to inspect or discuss their property needs however we strongly recommend that any potential attendee re-consider or delay an inspection/private appointment to inspect or a general appointment with one of our staff if they are feeling unwell with symptoms of COVID 19, or had contact with any person who has been diagnosed with COVID 19 or recently returned from overseas travel.
Visit: Department of Health - Australian Government - Symptoms

Description:
Outstanding potential in sought after Northcote
*** CONTACT AGENT TO ARRANGE A PRIVATE VIEWING ***
Resting on land, approximately 509sqm in the prized Northcote High zone this classic three bedroom brick home delivers exciting renovation/extension or new home site potential (STCA). Stroll to All Nations Park, Northcote Plaza, schools and city transport.
- Bright, open plan living space features 3 meter ceilings
- Low maintenance backyard enjoys sunny northerly aspect
- A covered bbq area with bluestone wood fire oven.
- Classic timber kitchen with stainless steel Glem gas stove
- Three comfortable, double size bedrooms, main has built-ins
- Period-style spa bathroom, shower and vanity, alarm
- Heating, manicured gardens, veggie gardens, wood fire oven
- Secure garage, off street driveway parking, rain water tank
- Close to Wales Street, vibrant cafes/restaurants
- Near All Nations Park, Northcote Plaza, schools, transport
*** COVID-19 Announcement ***
In our endeavours to look after the health and wellbeing of our people, our clients, our families and visitors, we ask that if you are attending an open for inspection, please adhere to the following:
Please do not enter the property if, you have returned from overseas in the past two weeks, you are unwell or have a fever and if you have come into contact with someone experiencing flu-like symptoms.
Under advisement from our Health Organisations, we ask that you please maintain a distance of 1.5 metres from others. Apply hand sanitiser as often as possible and please refrain from touching household items, such as door handles, cupboards and tapware etc.
Registration will be required to enter. If you cannot enter the property and are still interested, please call the agent and they will provide more information or alternate viewing options.
Please copy the below link for further information, Thank you:
https://www.mcgrath.com.au/advice/articles/coronavirus-business-operations-update
